</div>
<p>The <b>crested lark</b> (<i>Galerida cristata</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lark" title="Lark">lark</a> distinguished from the other 81 species of lark by the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crest_(feathers)" title="Crest (feathers)">crest of feathers</a> that rise up in territorial or courtship displays and when singing. Common to mainland <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">Europe</a>, the birds can also be found in northern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Africa" title="Africa">Africa</a> and in parts of western <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asia" title="Asia">Asia</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China" title="China">China</a>. It is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-migratory" title="Non-migratory" class="mw-redirect">non-migratory</a> bird, but can occasionally be found as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vagrancy_(biology)" title="Vagrancy (biology)">vagrant</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Britain" title="Great Britain">Great Britain</a>.</p>
<p></p>
